Hi, it's going to be by implementing a provable identity framework function in Haven1 network, During the transaction validation process, Haven1’s network validators will be required to verify the user’s wallet address against the anonymized data stored on the blockchain. This checkpoint ensures that the user is not the subject of sanctions or other regulatory restrictions. 
If participants have not completed the required identity verifications, transactions will not be accepted by validators. If a user becomes the subject of regulatory restrictions, their ability to use the network will be restricted to withdrawal requests only.

There's 3 certainties in life:
1. Crypto ain't going anywhere
2. We're all gonna make it
3. There's a separate channel for price talks 😜
